    "reasoning": "The number of anti-palindromes less than \(3^{12}\) with no consecutive equal digits in base 3 is found by counting valid sequences of lengths 1 to 12. For each length \(L\), the count depends on \(m = \lceil L/2 \rceil\) and follows the recurrence \(f(m) = f(m-1) + 2f(m-2)\) with \(f(1)=1\), \(f(2)=3\). Summing over lengths gives \(b_1 = 126\). Then \(k = b_1 + 27 = 153\), so \(k-18 = 135\). For a circle of 135 numbers where each is one more than the gcd of its neighbors, the only solution uses only the numbers 2 and 3 in a pattern where every third number is 3. The sum is \(2 \times (2 \times 135/3) + 3 \times (135/3) = 315\).",
